cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with information theory and optimal control theory to derive structural properties of optimal channel input distributions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with stochastic optimal control theory, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of variational equalities and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of the results to Multiple Input Multiple Output Gaussian Linear Channel Models suggests that the paper may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with settling long-standing problems in information theory, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
